org.team751.utils

Class Navigator

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.team751.utils.PeriodicTask
      • org.team751.utils.Navigator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    LiveWindowSendable, Sendable

    public class Navigator
extends PeriodicTask
implements Sendable, LiveWindowSendable
    This subsystem-like class keeps track of the robot's location relative to its starting point. The coordinate system is defined based on the initial location of the robot when it is started, or when reset() was last called. The origin of this coordinate system is at the robot's initial location. It does not rotate when the robot turns.
    Author:
    Sam Crow
